text:
in my science class, last year as an end of the week relaxer we’d watch an episode of the netflix show ‘cosmos’ with the show host, neil degrasse. he’s an american astrophysicist, author, and science communicator. i went home the first time after watching the show and explained to my dad how inspiring this man was and just how cool. there have been 3 sexual assault and sexual harassment allegations made against him. the case hasn’t been looked into very much since the allegations were made thursday, but this just showed me no matter who someone is or what they’ve done for the world- someone could do something as bad as this. when i first read the article on buzzfeed i was shocked and doubted it for some reason. but this is our world. i’m not saying every famous person will be accused of assault. i’m not saying every man who has contributed something good to the world is bad. i’m saying no matter what, everyone should be held accountable for their actions. and it shouldn’t be put into consideration who they are or what they’ve done. everyone should have the same verdict in the end.
•
•
•

text_retweet:
#repost from @khadija_gbla with @regram.app ... addressing different types of violence against women. “violence against women takes many forms, and occurs in various settings. different types of violence are not mutually exclusive, and women may experience more than one form of violence perpetrated by the same person. it is important to acknowledge that not all forms of violence fit conventional understandings of domestic and family violence, and that tackling violence against women must be sensitive to the variety of experiences of victim/survivors.

sexual violence remains subsumed under the definition of domestic and family violence, which contributes to the invisibility of this issue. while the #metoo movement has highlighted the prevalence of experiences of sexual violence, there is much to be done in giving greater prioritisation and visibility to this gross human rights violation in the policy space. an integrated approach for the prevention of and responses to sexual violence, including comprehensive sexuality education, and education about gender and respectful relationships. law reform and policy development should focus on measures to enhance safe mechanisms of disclosure, promote reporting and evidence collection, and challenge harmful community, police and judicial attitudes towards sexual violence.

other forms of violence against women that are excluded from the focus on a conventional understanding of domestic and family violence include trafficking and sexual exploitation, early and forced marriage, dowry abuse, and labour, domestic and/or sexual servitude. responses to these forms of violence must be co-designed with diverse communities and groups, and ensure access to services no matter whether there is an intention to press charges or not. manifestations of violence such as reproductive coercion, forced sterilisation of women with disability, and medically unnecessary procedures on intersex infants and children need to be within the scope of efforts to end violence against women.

text:
“why are the girls there? why did they go, why do they, to these parties where everyone knows what happens? let me tell you why: because i was there too...”
—cynthia robinson, “girlplay,” in the american fraternity, by andrew moisey
•
this unique, provocative treasure of a book, already sold out online and heading into a second printing, forces a hard look at an aspect of university culture unique to these (barely) united states 🇺🇸.
•
one that casts a long and broad shadow—at times an uncomfortably racist and misogynistic one—across our entire country and culture, reaching all the way up into the stratosphere of economic and political power, decades after the college experience has been lived.
•
it was my privilege and my honor to contribute the essay “girlplay” to this worthy project, at the invitation of my colleague and friend, @realandrewmoisey .
•
every college student, every prospective college student, the parents of anyone in or heading to college, and — of course — anyone with the power to nominate a supreme court judge, or vote in favor of or against the approbation of same, needs to read this book.
•
needs to be _required_ to read this book.
•
i’ll eventually get this essay up onto my site, but for the moment it’s accessible here.
•
please share if you’re so inclined.
•
thanks to @buffalostreetbooks for hosting us today and providing the forum for a great discussion.
•
•
•

—cynthia robinson, “girlplay,” in the american fraternity, by andrew moisey
•
this unique, provocative treasure of a book, already sold out online and heading into a second printing, forces a hard look at an aspect of university culture unique to these (barely) united states 🇺🇸.
•
one that casts a long and broad shadow—at times an uncomfoably racist and misogynistic one—across our entire country and culture, reaching all the way up into the stratosphere of economic and political power, decades after the college experience has been lived.
•
it was my privilege and my honor to contribute the essay “girlplay” to this wohy project, at the invitation of my colleague and friend,  .
•
every college student, every prospective college student, the parents of anyone in or heading to college, and — of course — anyone with the power to nominate a supreme cou judge, or vote in favor of or against the approbation of same, needs to read this book.
•
needs to be _required_ to read this book.
•
i’ll eventually get this essay up onto my site, but for the moment it’s accessible here.
•
please share if you’re so inclined.
•
thanks to  for hosting us today and providing the forum for a great discussion.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
this is what a ptsd breakthrough looks like. 
7 years ago i stopped driving. i was 17 trying to get my licence. at first i blamed it on college; i moved out of town during the time i was learning, freshman weren't allowed to have cars on campus. but as the years went on i never pursued getting a car or getting my licence. 
7 years ago i was sexually assaulted by my driving instructor. he was a grown man in his forties and he took advantage of a naive girl. i secretly didn't want to pursue driving because i didn't want to be brought back to that place. before i was assaulted i loved driving; i was a little paranoid with my bpd and mood swing/dissociation, but it was relaxing for me. .
tonight i was supposed to go out and have a girl's night with one of my son's aunts. it was getting late when we got together and we didn't feel like doing much so she offered to take me pokémon hunting (we're avid #pokemongo players, there's not much else to do when you're sober in this town). when we got in the car she offered to let me drive. my heart was racing, something in my gut felt like i was ready and she was the right person to trust this with. .
i drove around an empty parking lot a thousand times, practiced parking and pulling up to the curb, and even drove up to 35 mph on the main road. it doesn't sound like a lot for someone who turns 25 next weekend, but this was a huge step for me. .
i feel like i can breathe again...a little manic, but free. i washed my face tonight, picked out my outfit for my trip to the city tomorrow, and i'm going to bed without feeling suicidal. these are big moves for me. .
now let's hope this energy flow lasts. here's to breaking the cycle and facing your demons. .
.
.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

check out red carpet photos from ebony magazine's annual power 100 galaâ  on friday night, ebony magazine had their annual power 100 gala which took place on in los angeles, ca.the magazine celebrated its 73rd anniversary this year and unveiled its prestigious annual ebony power 100 list for 2018. among those honoured are #metoo founder, tarana burke, stacey abrams, the first black georgia democratic gubernatorial nominee (honored in the disruptors category); andrew gillum, mayor of tallahassee and the first black candidate for governor of florida (honored in disruptors category); keisha lance bottoms, the second black female mayor of atlanta (honored in the women up category); and london breed, the first black female lgbt mayor of san francisco (also honored in the women up category). other celebrities in attendance included cari champion , neyo, eva marcelle , saweetie, cynthia bailey, yolanda adams, chris tucker, adienne baillion and husband israel houghton, david oyelowo, and kat graham.see red carpet photos below.the post check out red carpet photos from ebony magazine's annual power 100 gala appeared first on linda ikeji blog.

text:
last night i went on a date with someone who isn’t my wife! i took our five year old daughter out for the evening. she wore one of her favourite dresses, i put on a shirt (pretty dressed up for me). i bought her flowers and we went out for dinner and to enjoy the christmas lights of regent street. 
we played games (eye spy and rock, paper, scissors mostly), tried to identify the animals in nevaeh’s ‘animal pasta’ and sung many songs. 
we had a really fun evening, which was of course the aim. 
there was also another aim. i have a natural instinct as a father, to wrap my kids up in cotton wool to keep them safe. shield them from the world; there is a certain extent to which i do this. however one day, she is going to fly the nest. she will go out into the world and live her own life. if i simply shelter her, i am not properly preparing her to stand on her own two feet. 
i see it as my duty as her dad to demonstrate her worth to her, through the way i treat her. to model the way she should expect all men to behave toward her. to have no question in her own mind of her value. 
this wasn’t a one off. we regularly have “daddy / daughter dates” (this was probably the most fancy so far!) i see myself as a feminist and a “masculinist”. the #metoo movement has brought dark, toxic and twisted masculinity into the light. i have made a lifelong commitment to try and show nevaeh (and jj) the strengths and the virtues of a different kind of masculinity. one that doesn’t suppress others but inspires and equips them to live life to its fullest. i aspire to live out those virtues in front of my kids every day! .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
every sunday morning, preachers all over the world insist that you give them your hard-earned money. excuse me, but if the church needs so much money to advance its cause, then why did jesus spend zero time asking people for money? .
.
why didn't jesus charge people for healings then? why didn't jesus charge the crowds to hear him speak like pastors do at conferences today? why didn't jesus take a salary like today's pastors do? why did jesus do everything freely? could it be because the work of god does not depend on money to succeed? .
.

why thank you @thetcn for showcasing such superb talent. i am left in awe of all the writers, directors, actors and producers - not forgetting the talented crew. without people like @jimmyakingbola @lil_bit_of_chiz @minnieayres @fraserayers diversity and inclusion wouldn’t have a platform in this crazy media industry - and now it does - god knows we love you (i’m passionate about this) i particularly loved the haven speech that talked about creating a society where were are not ‘survivors’ (of tragedy - like the #metoo campaign) but finding the root of the social issue.... 🙌🏻thank you to @c_a_j_cole who was my wingman and has inspired me a i love you and of course to @theartistnamedjordan who i look forward to working with again. 
i love these guys, they are game changers big up everyone involved at @bafta 🎥 🎞 and all the winners and entries - now we just need to get some of these films shown on the @bbc 🤪

i’m wearing a dress by @inthestyle boots by @andotherstories and tan by @stmoriz which got darker by the hour - soz! 😬

day 8 | december 02 
sexual consent is  an  agreement to participate in sexual activity between two adults (over the legal age of 18). it is a vital  concept that needs to be understood when it comes to intimate relations between men and women as it must be freely given, reversible, informed, enthusiastic and specific. when there is no consent, it is sexual violation or rape.

if you are forced to have sex against your will, if you say no, asleep, unconscious, under the influence of alcohol or a controlled drug or substance - you cannot give your consent and you have been sexually assaulted.

no means no! hear word! .

text:
nadia murad is an iraqi yazidi woman who survived the worst cruelties ever inflicted on her and her community, the yazidis of iraq. during her ordeal she was held captive and repeatedly gang raped, tortured & beaten. the terrorists organised slave markets for selling off the women & girls and yazidi women were forced to renounce their religion. 
she became an activist after escaping in 2014, campaigning to help put an end to human trafficking and calling on the world to take a tougher line on rape as a weapon of war. 
she is un's first goodwill ambassador for survivors of human trafficking and winner of the nobel peace prize. 
we salute nadia murad for showing and encouraging many women to #standupforyourself

text:
the journey of life is amazing, we travel along it and experience so many things that can be positive and negative... the most important aspect is how we deal with those experiences as that is what shapes us in our own story.

i for one do not regret anything that has happened on my journey, everything has been a learning curve that has helped me grow and become the person i am today and i am so so so grateful for that as i have lived and learnt and continue to live and learn. i am the embodiment of love and feel blessed for that realisation.

whoever is in my life is meant to be and the relationships that i have right now amaze me and are pure and loving, whoever is no longer in my life also amaze me as i have learnt so much from them and am happy that they came into my life taught me and i choose to remove them .

love your journey and just be as that will serve you to the next level.

text:
mistä tänä vuonna puhuttiin? mitkä aiheet ja uutiset mullistivat maailmaa, ajatteluamme ja toimintaamme? 
ilmastonmuutos, muovin määrä meressä, teknologian piilovalta, sodat ja me too -liike. siinä hs:n toimituksen valitsemat vuoden 2018 merkittävimmät uutisaiheet. 
koska uutiset usein kertovat rumia totuuksia maailmasta, hs suunnitteli rumat jouluvillapaidat ilmentämään vuoden tärkeimpiä aiheita. 
hs vie joulupaitoja aihepiirien asiantuntijoille ja vaikuttajille, kuten martti ahtisaarelle ja elina knihtilälle,  ja kysyy heiltä ratkaisuja, joilla rumista totuuksista tulee vähän kauniimpia. miten maailma muuttuu paremmaksi?

text:
the irony of depression is that the more depressed you feel, the more you want to be alone. the more alone you feel, the more depressed you become.
➖➖➖
people often ask me how i overcame depression. first off, much like an eating disorder, i don’t think i’ll ever overcome it. it’s always around the corner and it especially comes up whenever i feel like i’m failing.
➖➖➖
however, the one thing i can say that has helped more than anything in the word is this: connecting. no - not connecting through messages or texts, i mean making the scary step and saying “yes” to that coffee catch up or “yes” to that dinner party where you don’t know anyone other than the host.
➖➖➖
when jen from @moderndaywoman asked me what i want to achieve with what i’m doing - it was a really simple answer; i said “this” (and pointed to her then myself). i’ve seen the magic that a simple connection can make. it can break down shame and create a level of confidence you would never expect, and certainly better than even the best rx that’s out there.
➖➖➖
so to everyone out there who is looking to beat depression, anxiety, an eating disorder or anything in between, know this: you are not alone in how you feel. and the sooner you can reach out to someone you trust and say “me too”, the closer you will be to living the kind of future you deserve to live.
➖➖➖
written only with love and kindness, dr kat x

è stato un lungo lavoro di scrittura, giorni in cui come una pazza mi aggiravo per la città parlando da sola mentre cercavo disperatamente di attivare la mia ormai scarsa memoria, e persino un'incursione di shopping per cercare di essere almeno carina. 
ma la mia fatica non è stata nulla a confronto con l'enorme lavoro del team di @tedxnovara capitanato dal vulcanico marco cigolotti. 
ho avuto l'onore di chiudere la x edizione e ho portato la storia delle storie: evelyn mchale simbolo dei tradimenti a tutte le donne dimenticate dal novecento.
è stata davvero un'emozione indimenticabile, arricchita dalla sorpresa di avere con me i miei amici ed editori teresa e riccardo di @semlibri

text: do you know how big the gender gap is in science, technology, engineering and maths (stem)? women only make up 14.4% of all people working in stem in the u.k. it has been shown that the cultural effects of attributing science subjects to boys and humanities to girls from a young age are a major factor in causing this divide. women earn nearly 1/3 less than men within a year of completing a phd in stem. have a look at www.stem.org.uk for the work being done to inspire a new generation of young women to go into the field. #womenkind

text:
zelda perkins is the former assistant of harvey weinstein and was one of the first women to attempt legal action against the producer while working at miramax in the late 1990s. silenced by a gagging order, she has since spoken out, instigating  a parliamentary inquiry into the unethical nature of non-disclosure agreements.
🇬🇧🇬🇧🇬🇧
breaking her nda in 2017 in the midst of the #metoo movement, perkins' campaign reveals that nda's are used far too often by wealthy and powerful men as a way to cover up their crimes, often including sexual misconduct, assault and rape. at the age of 23, while at the venice film festival, perkins confronted weinstein after he had attempted to rape one of her colleagues, (he had previously made unwanted advances towards perkins as well). of course, weinstein denied all of their accusations, and shortly after, the two women quit their jobs and spoke to solicitors - this was at least 20 years ago. but her lawyer, unconvinced they’d be able to win a case against miramax and disney (also weinstein’s company), urged perkins’ to take the nda, which offered her £125,000 (this nda can be viewed online). perkins had to quit the film industry after she was then blacklisted by weinstein. she was not even able to have a copy of the nda, and neither woman was allowed to speak to a therapist. although perkins received a lot of money from the agreement, it has to be remembered that the money was a small amount to weinstein, but a large sum for perkins - an example of how money and influence can silence information that should be public knowledge. there’s a clear power imbalance, one that allowed weinstein to repeat his misconduct over and over again and bully women into accepting a gagging order rather than speaking out. ~~~
speaking to emily maitlis on @bbc newsnight, perkins explained how the legal system had no way of protecting them and quashed their voices. she explains: 'the problem with the nda is that it has been weaponised by powerful people and by lawyers. we need to have a framework where people can work safely and where there is recourse when these individuals abuse power.'
name: EncyclopediaofCourageousWomen

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies. 
they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green, author
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text:
जहाँ एक तरफ बड़े बड़े देश पोस्टर्स लेकर रैलियां निकलते फिरते हैं, वही दूसरी और हमारे देश में इन बातों पर बात करना गलत सा मन जाता है। जब कोई व्यक्ति इसके बारे में बात करना चाहता हो तोह उसे "शह्ह्ह्ह" करके चुप होने को कह दिया जाता है। यानि यह साफ दिखता है की लोग hiv एवं aids के बारे में बात करने से हिचकिचाते हैं। हमें ऐसा लगता है की अब समय आ गया है जब हमें इसके लिए कुछ करना चाहिए।  __________________

translation:

in a world where every year on 1st december, everyone celebrates world aids day, ngo jeevan arth foundation thinks that the way people in the country don’t know about hiv/aids and the way there is a lack of awareness, we feel that we need to do efforts everyday to make an awareness amongst our people.

on one side, people around the globe raise their voices, pick posters and take out rallies for hiv/aids awareness. meanwhile on the other side, people in our country find it wrong to talk about such issues.

they don’t feel like addressing such issues. whenever someone wants to talk about this topic or someone is talking on such a topic, they’re hushed and asked to lower their voices. as if, it’s a taboo to talk about hiv and aids.

people find it uncomfortable to talk about hiv and this makes us more vulnerable to such diseases.

ngo jeevan arth foundation thinks that it’s time we did something on this.

#jeevanarthfoundation #ngo #india #rajasthan #jaipur #womenempowerment #metoo #childeducation #girlchild #womensrights #equality #rights #education #society #dogood #philanthropist #socialservice #socialwelfare #worldaidsday
name: Jeevan Arth Foundation (NGO)

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
⚠️cringe alert, lol⚠️ i found a photo gallery yesterday i hadn't been able to access for yearsss. i forgot nearly every single photo had even been taken! they're full of more cringe, more emo than 2007 myspace even knew what to do with, lol, but this is more than just a trip down memory lane.
.
i've been wrestling a lot w/ identity -- who am i, what's my voice, who's my community, is who i am dictated by what i know about me or what's reflected back to me in how others relate to and interact w/ me? so many questions after a year of my life and body radically shifting beneath my feet. all of these photos were from age 18-19, just one year -- and as you can see i lived a hundred lifetimes in that time. fighting for the safety to be herself. a tomboy badass, who despised being a girl in every possible way, trapped in a world demanding nothing but delicate, feminine, pretty, christian, driven, pure. that dissonance amplified the agony and made the plunges into the darkness all the more drastic. masking as a hyperfeminine, gentle girl only reminded me of the abuse given to me bc of both those very qualities. ..but exploring the alternative was dangerous, unsafe, put a target on my back. at this point i was clawing to get out; i broke. so, i tried.
.
now, i'm trying to find me again. a queer, adrogynous creative; an artist. i'm edgy, tough, a bit of a bamf. i also live and breathe compassion, empathy, nurture, love. i'm a scientist, a realist, still feel like an athlete inside. i'm an educator, an advocate, owner of a very broken body. i'm sick. i'm also a survivor, who's felt pure unimaginable evil and come out alive. i'm also so many things no one even knows about, but they're still in there. in me.
.
i haven't found me fully again, it'll be awhile. but, it makes it hard to laugh too hard at this mess of a kidd above. on one hand, she feels like an alien to me. someone i don't know and have never met in my life. but i also feel so close to her in that brutal place where you're trying to find yourself but trauma keeps changing who you are before you've even gotten to know the last girl. ..it's rough.
.
i hope we both get there. until then, enjoy the  laughs.
.
🙃🎭🖤

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: "to be clear, this is a movement about the 1 in 4 girls and the 1 in 6 boys who are sexually assaulted every year and who carry those wounds into adulthood. it’s about the 84 percent of trans women who will be sexually assaulted this year. and the indigenous women who are three and a half times more likely to be sexually assaulted than any other group. or people with disabilities who are seven times more likely to be sexually abused. it’s about the 60 percent of black girls like me who will be experiencing sexual violence before they turn 18. and the thousands and thousands of low-wage workers who are being sexually harassed right now on jobs that they can’t afford to quit." she added that the world is experiencing “collective trauma” in the wake of #metoo and that what we do with that trauma will determine whether the movement can truly effect change. “this accumulation of feelings that so many of us are experiencing together, across the globe, is collective trauma. but it is also the first step towards actively building a world that we want right now,” burke said. “what we do with this thing that we’re all holding is the evidence that this is bigger than a moment. it’s the confirmation that we are in a movement.”

what does being strong mean to me? i am a domestic abuse survivor. being strong to me means everything. #strongis freedom. living my power. not being afraid. being strong inside and outside. feeling safe. being confident. speaking my heart and my mind. being passionate. doing the work. bringing positive energy. #strongis loyalty. commitment. integrity. honesty. love. not saying sorry for being strong, confident and smart. saying no. being #fitasbuck. being my word #liftingheavyshit. #liftingmoreheavyshit #changingtheworld being a stand for girls and women to live in a world without physical and emotional domestic abuse, sexual harassment and rape. to be whoever they want to be. female leaders. being a stand for the #strongmen who support and love #strongwomen. being the change for the next generation of girls and women, boys and men to live freely, safely and as they want to. celebrating girls and women for being #strongasfuck #strongis what ever the hell we want being strong to be! #strongisme
.

text:
seriously? 
she was charged with 'inciting debauchery'. give us a break. she was attending an award ceremony, and she wore a dress that showed a bit of body. seriously dudes. get a grip. at most she was inciting publicity for her movies. -
when oh when will all of these antiquated, outdated, way too often enshrined in religious precepts, designed to diminish women, systems of thought and practice be wiped off the face of the earth?
-
i know this is such a smaller news issue than the much much much larger issue of millions of women and girls experiencing violence or constraints because of their gender in every country every day. but it is symptomatic. and illustrates how embedded the mental models of control of women are.
-
so in fact, there is inciting to be done. 
let's consciously incite women's rights change work! 
the work of our own agency, of freeing up mindsets, of living without the daily background worry of safety, of changing outdated legal systems of inequity, of achieving equal pay for same work, of having full control of what we do with and to our bodies without interference from governments, of continuing to gain equal rights in realm after realm after realm. 
and yes, of even including in our mission the right to wear whatever trendy or silly outfit we damn well please without having to worry about the behavioral or ethical choices of others. and even, if we are to of inciting consensual debauchery. -
#changemakers #equalrights #feminist #equalpay #womensrights #womenagentsofchange #timesup #metoo #equality

text:
a woman's perspective // hawick // tuesday 4th december
.
i've been asked to speak in the scottish borders this coming tuesday as part of the annual 16 days of activism event. each year, organisations across the globe host events to raise awareness of gender-based violence. as some of the women in my series nevertheless, she persisted have been affected by various forms of gendered abuse (child, sexual and domestic), i have been asked to share stories from the series and talk about what i have learned from all 25 women.
.
the talk is free and open to all. the event will run from 11am-3pm with my talk starting at noon. books will be available to purchase on the day for £5.
.
please share with all your friends in the borders!
.

text:
hi to anyone who stumbled across this page!! i’m creating this page to help myself connect more with others during my own journey. a little information about me: ———————————————————————————🍃 i have experienced sexual assault twice in my life. once as a child by a relative and once in college. i’m in the process of working through it with my therapist and pursuing emdr in january 🙌🙌 ———————————————————————————🍃 the single element that has helped me the most (so far) is connection with others and sharing my story (thus why i created this page). also, maybe if i can help anyone else through my journey, that would be very meaningful for me.
———————————————————————————🍃 i’m the first to admit that #traumawork is kind of the worst, but certainly the only way out is through.
———————————————————————————🍃 i tend to deal with my own trauma through the use of disordered eating, working on that. i’ll do my best to make sure that i keep this page trigger free. and i’m in an in an ambivalent stage of whether or not i want to work through that. because unfortunately that way of dealing is really effective and easy. #edrecovery #edwarrior #bodydysmorphia ———————————————————————————🍃healing certainly isn’t linear (unfortunately 🤦🏻‍♀️🤦🏻‍♀️) but i’m doing the best i can to connect with others when i’m triggered
———————————————————————————🍃i believe any survivors stories and i applaud you for the work you do and truly believe you can make it through anything #metoo #metoomovement ———————————————————————————🍃currently the most inspiring and helpful accounts for me in my journey are @catielynchlcsw @revelatori @lindseyhallwrites & @drcolleenreichmann ladies, thanks for all you do and put out there!! you truly make a difference to me and i admire each of you for your strength and vulnerability

text:
your silence speaks volumes, 
i hear every word you don't say. 
your silence is deadly, 
it killed my love for you. 
your silence filled me with sadness, 
i'll never be the same. 
your silence is reckless, 
you know not what you do. 
your silence, it broke me,
my heart is torn in two.

your silence,
it's over. -crg

#poem #myheart #truth #love #life #poetry #heal #story #metoo #abuse #rape #recover #my #art #forgive

text:
#burningbush during his tenure in the navy, bush was stationed with torpedo squadron 51 aboard the uss san jacinto. on august 1, 1944 his unit launched an operation against the japanese in the bonin islands. on september 2, 1944, bush’s aircraft was downed leading to the death of eight navy airmen, leaving bush as the lone survivor. the episode later became known as the chichijima incident and led to the future president being hailed as a war hero.

political career

upon graduating from yale, bush began his career in politics and was elected chairman of the harris county, texas republican party in 1963. three years later, bush was elected to the us house of representatives, marking the beginning of a meteoric rise which resulted in him being named director of the central intelligence agency in 1976.

before he was named head of the cia, bush was already heavily involved in covert operations according a book released in 2010, by author russ baker. in his book, family of secrets: the bush dynasty, america’s invisible government, and the hidden history of the last fifty years baker revealed the relationship between bush and former president richard nixon. a relationship, the author asserts, that eventually led to the watergate scandal and nixon’s resignation. 
as director of the cia, bush was responsible for overseeing the payment of hundreds of thousands of dollars to panamanian leader and suspected cocaine trafficker, manuel noriega. although bush claimed he wasn’t aware of noriega’s illicit activities until 1988, the cia’s involvement in latin america would eventually end in a national controversy during the reagan administration, in what became known as the iran-contra scandal.

while bush served less than a year as the head of the cia, he was also caught destroying evidence of us war crimes. as reported by muckrock, “declassified records recently unearthed in crest show the cia waffled on a promise to obey the law in destroying records of agency’s illegal activities and wrongdoing.” four years after serving as the director of the cia, george h.w. bush was elected vice president of the united states. serving under former president ronald reagan, bush kept a

text:
on one of my remaining nights in lisbon, i had some unfinished business to take care of.  i dodged out into the city, and dove into the cloudy, rainy night and headed to the water….to gather rocks. rocks to mark with memories, and awareness. .
.
i love tradition. i crave closure. i seek ways to “mark” a time and place, and memories.  these rocks will serve me well. they are resting by the ocean.
.
.
lisbon’s beauty offered me a place to let go of some stuff that has been reflecting back at me, from when trauma first occurred.  we all have these external happenings that begin to engage our deepest need for affirmation and sacred love, but instead become harmful reminders that what was done somehow was a reflection of our worth (lie). .
.
i learned self-hate by listening to the message of the harm done to me and all the complexities that came with it. trauma does not teach you that what was done to you was wrong.  it teaches you that it somehow was your fault, or that you somehow invited it in. .
.
i can safely say, that i have become my biggest advocate. i am constantly learning new ways to slow down, connect and be aware of the reality of what is going on inside of me, and what needs to happen next to further the growth. .
.
i sat and reflected on much of those inner messages that i need to let go of. they included constant thoughts that haunt me, and areas of my life that i need to leave behind. .
.
on my last evening in portugal, i wondered to the ocean at sunset, rocks in hand. each marked with the crippling messages or actions that have continually paused further growth. .
.
one by one, while the sunset posed as the backdrop, i tossed the rocks and their messages in the ocean... to celebrate that i no longer have a place for them. .
.
if this resonates with you, then please grab your rocks. mark them, and know that you have permission to move towards the places where you find yourself adored, cherished, and loved in the most sacred ways…toss the rocks far from you…. hold your hunger for genuine desire in a new light without those old messages, and know you are not and never have been alone in your search for belonging safe and sacred…

“i looked around and i didn’t see enough women represented in the food world. you had the food network women and that was it. the media was filled with women but they were so excited to write about the “bro” culture”, they weren’t lifting their own up. it extended to the coverage in magazines, on websites, t.v. shows, the documentaries. 👩🏾‍🍳 even more damaging is it extends to awards. when you get a big award, things follow; money, investors, marketing opportunities, p.r. people. that’s how chefs make money and amass power. when it’s a bunch of white guys, other groups are not getting those same opportunities.” -kerry diamond on what motivated her to start cherry bombe, the food publication that elevates the stories of inspiring female entrepreneurs. 🚺

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still, today, right now.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

a non

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still, today, right now.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

@regran_ed from @soquerotreinar -  em uma pesquisa realizada pela campanha chega de fiu fiu em 2013, das 7.762 mulheres ouvidas, 81% afirmaram que já deixaram de fazer alguma coisa por medo de assédio. de acordo com uma pesquisa do instituto yougo, 86% das brasileiras já sofreram assédio em público, sendo:
⚠️ 77% assovios,
⚠️ 74% olhares insistentes,
⚠️ 57% comentários de cunho sexual e
⚠️ 39% xingamentos.
😡 50% dessas mulheres afirmou que já foram seguidas na rua;
😡 44% já tiveram seus corpos tocados;
😡 37% relataram que homens se exibiram para elas e
😡 08% foram estupradas em locais públicos.
.

text:
big tw for #transphobia #sexism and rape talk.

sometimes it's too painful to tell our own stories--but it's even more painful to be erased from their tellings. it was a different time when @hilaryswank was casted in #boysdontcry , the film and true story of #brandonteena hit home for me as a trans boy, a rape survivor, a midwesterner, as someone who has had life on the line, as someone who has been called on the phone just to be called faggot. moving forward, if you're gonna better and kill us on screen, at least hire the people who have survived it all. it may not be the 90s anymore, but many of us, especially those from/in #trumpsamerica , still follow brandon's life trajectory until the end.

to the right is a #remixed scene from the film holding my own pain and the pain of my community. big love to @thestudioact and @bradcalcaterra for your caring direction of the piece, and @joslyn.defreece for going there with the most understanding anyone could ever have. big love to the actors & creatives who are working on this very thing in big ways right now; we need you 💜💜💜, @loganrozos @tracelysette
@lavernecox @rhysernst @silash .
.
.
.

text:
despite the fact that ethlyne clair (born november 23, 1904) was probably one of the most beautiful women ever to grace the screen during the late 1920s/early 1930s, she never became a star.
•
ethlyne made her break for stardom after winning a beauty contest in her home town of talladega, alabama, and headed to new york to find work as an extra (her first role of note was in sandra (1924) starring barbara la marr). •
•
in hollywood, she signed a contract with universal; appearing in a handful of comedies shorts, including the newlyweds, followed by a spate of westerns opposite hoot gibson. •
•
in 1928, she married her agent, richard lonsdale hinshaw, in mexico. it was an unhappy union; she later revealed he forced her into marriage at gunpoint. her career also waned, after playing second fiddle to rex, the wonder horse, she left universal, and freelanced. it was pathé, representing a variety of independent film studios, who nominated her as one of the years wampas baby stars of 1929. the accolade kept her in the press; she was also one of hollywood’s first stars to launch her own beauty care range. it was this which brought her to the attention of ernest westmore, of the hollywood make-up dynasty.
•
divorced from her husband, her marriage to ernest wasn’t without drama; when at their wedding, his first wife showed up with their daughter, muriel, dressed in rags to highlight the state of poverty ernest had left them in. ernest in turn flew at photographers; got into a brawl and was arrested. as his career flourished, ethlyne’s went into a deep decline; her temporary contract with warner bros. had expired and she was out of work. later, in 1991, she claimed that mogul daryl zanuck ruined her career after she refused his sexual advances. •
•
by 1934, with her film career over, she tried her hand on the stage with limited results. instead, divorced from ernest, she married again, to a second-hand car salesman, and retired to raise her family. she died in february 1996, aged 91.
•
•

in 1928, she married her agent, richard lonsdale hinshaw, in mexico. it was an unhappy union; she later revealed he forced her into marriage at gunpoint. her career also waned, after playing second fiddle to rex, the wonder horse, she left universal, and freelanced. it was pathé, representing a variety of independent film studios, who nominated her as one of the years wampas baby stars of 1929. the accolade kept her in the press; she was also one of hollywood’s first stars to launch her own beauty care range. it was this which brought her to the attention of ernest westmore, of the hollywood make-up dynasty.
•
divorced from her husband, her marriage to ernest wasn’t without drama; when at their wedding, his first wife showed up with their daughter, muriel, dressed in rags to highlight the state of povey ernest had left them in. ernest in turn flew at photographers; got into a brawl and was arrested. as his career flourished, ethlyne’s went into a deep decline; her temporary contract with warner bros. had expired and she was out of work. later, in 1991, she claimed that mogul daryl zanuck ruined her career after she refused his sexual advances. •
•
by 1934, with her film career over, she tried her hand on the stage with limited results. instead, divorced from ernest, she married again, to a second-hand car salesman, and retired to raise her family. she died in february 1996, aged 91.
•
•

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
a recent online survey revealed that around 78% victims of workplace sexual harassment in india don’t report the crime. one of the main reasons for keeping silent is fear of losing their job. .
.
while this is understandable in today’s competitive job market, it is important to remember that your silence is what will allow the perpetrator to continue with his or her harmful actions. .
.
so, don’t let fear of losing your job stop you from doing what is right. pledge to show zero tolerance for sexual harassment now! .

text:
⬅️ forts. fra forrige innlegg
juletreet sto upyntet skeivt på juletrefoten, og vi måtte bare gå i gang med å bære ut flaskene, tømte askebegrene, vaske og tørke. jeg husker at vi lå på knær og støvsugde det store hvite teppet mamma var så stolt av, for hun likte teppet best når trådene stod rett opp. dette var vår jobb, og stakkars oss om vi lot være. da kunne hun være sint og sur i dagevis, kjefte og smelle, mobbe i det ene øyeblikket for å overse oss i det neste. det gjorde vondt langt inn i hjertet, for vi var så glad i henne. jeg var 8 år og så redd, sint og anspent, at jeg begynte å tisse i senga. min mor og «knappemannen» levde et merkelig liv. likeverdige som slåsskjemper, for så å knulle som gale når de hadde en «god periode». alt dette var hennes scene, og vi var tilskuere. og var vi ikke våken når dramatikken skjedde, så ble vi vekket. «kom og se jenter, nå skal tullingen henge seg i trappa». hun lo høyt og ondskapsfullt, klappet i hendene, mens han fomlet med tauet. dette er bare en av mange minner som sitter spikret. hun valgte ham før oss, og hun valgte alkoholen, hatet, sjalusien, overgrepene, og alt som alkoholmisbruket førte med seg. nå sier ikke jeg at du ikke skal kose deg med litt alkohol i jula — jeg gjør det selv. men jeg mener også at vi som voksne må være klar over at mange barn gruer seg til jul, og at det som du kanskje mener er uskyldige moro, er noe barnet ditt opplever som utrygt. hvordan vil du bli husket? har du tenkt over hvilke minner du vil gi videre?
.

text:
i løpet av 20 år har forbruket av alkohol økt med rundt 40 prosent. i mange familier, og for mange barn, setter et høyt alkoholforbruk dype spor, akkurat slik det har gjort det i mitt liv. med alkoholen kom de stygge ordene, volden, overgrepene, smerten og fortielsen. hvis nesten alle drikker mer, vil flere av oss trå over terskelen der vi tar skade eller skader andre. jeg har lyst til å dele med deg en typisk skrekkens jul fra min barndom. jeg gjør det sammen med disse vakre bildene fra bymarka i dag, slik at du ser hvor jeg ofte finner roen. mine friminutt, sammen med noen gode pulstopper, er jeg helt avhengig av for å kunne holde skyggene fra barndommen på avstand. før jeg deler må jeg fortelle at jeg har brutt med min mor for nesten 20 år siden. hun har aldri anerkjent min historie, hun har aldre angret noe, og hun har nå gjort meg arveløs som straff for at jeg ikke har latt meg kue til taushet. som barn var vi vant til at huset ofte var full av folk. ville fester, slåsskamper mellom min mor, og min stefar, dvs. han med de blanke knappene... pornoblader som stakk ut av skuffer og skap, forskjellige menn vi kunne finne henne sammen med, den evige røykskodda, og fulle fremmede på sengekanten vår om natta. jeg husker at lillesøster og jeg måtte rydde etter fyllefestene. jeg husker spesielt en julaften morgen hvor stua så ut som innsiden av det berømte «bomba horhuset»..... forts. neste innlegg ➡️
.

text:
voilà, je l’ai vu. 15 jours que je me motive car je savais que ça serait difficile, compliqué. .
et cela aurait été tellement dommage de ne pas le voir. .
@andrea_bescond a adapté pour le cinéma sa pièce les chatouilles ou la danse de la colère, inspirée de sa propre douleur d’enfance.  l’agression sexuelle, le viol. .
jouant le rôle principal, elle nous expose cette souffrance, indélébile, aussi bien psychologiquement que physiquement. le corps enregistre. il garde tout en mémoire. l’exutoire de la danse, exprimant cette rage, cette colère ne suffit plus. la parole seule peut, doucement, pas à pas libérer. mais à la condition qu’elle reçoive une écoute. .
.
la réalisation est particulièrement soignée, tellement esthétique, mêlant les scènes chez la psy aux souvenirs, aux fantasmes, à la réalité. cet esthétique mêlée à la danse envoie ce miroir de violence contenue, ce dark side qui envahit tout, jusqu’à ce qu’on ne puisse plus. .
il n’y a pas de prescription à la douleur et à la souffrance. .
merci @andrea_bescond . merci infiniment pour cette justesse, ce témoignage implacable. merci.
.

.

il n’y a pas de prescription à la douleur et à la souffrance. .
merci  . merci infiniment pour cette justesse, ce témoignage implacable. merci.

text:
letztens habe ich nebenbei von einer statistik gehört, die ich erst nicht glauben wollte.
es sind mehr männer die thomas heißen in führungspositionen, als überhaupt frauen.
doch wer ist daran schuld? naja. einige männer sagen, »dass es doch nach leistung gehe und nicht nach geschlecht«. einige frauen sagen, dass »die männer« gerne unter sich und einfach über »den frauen« stehen wollen. aber weil mich das thema tief gehender interessiert, suchte ich nach einem buch.

nach zahlreichen twitter-empfehlungen griff ich nach »die letzten tage des patriarchats« von margarete stokowski (@marga_owski). ein junge dame, die für spiegel online texte schreibt und nun ihre veröffentlichten artikel, in überarbeiteter version inkl. anmerkungen in gebundener form anbietet.

in ihrem buch stellt die durch die einzelnen artikel die familiäre und gesellschaftliche systemfrage nach dem patriarchat.

doch was ist eigentlich das patriarchat?
nunja, das patriachat ist, laut wikipedia, eine »gesellschaftsordnung, bei der der mann eine bevorzugte stellung in staat und familie innehat und bei der in erbfolge und sozialer stellung die männliche linie ausschlaggebend ist.«
für mich geht das patriarchat allerdings noch viel weiter. und zwar so weit, dass unseren geschlechtern farben, berufe, tätigkeiten und ja, sogar autos zugewiesen werden. »wie kann man denn nur als mann in der pflege arbeiten und einen mini fahren?« so, oder so ähnlich sind die bestimmungen, an denen wir uns messen müssen. 
müssen wir das? ja. 
sollten wir das? nein.

gerade in unseren sich sehr starke verändernden leistungsgesellschaft, gibt es nicht nur diese vorgefertigten schubladen, in die jeder rein passen muss, sondern auch viele ungerechtigkeiten gegenüber dem weiblichen geschlecht. #metoo hat es gezeigt.
dieses buch lässt jeden den einstieg finden ohne den humor zu vergessen und verschafft männer das nötige verständnis.
#feminismus #smashpatricarchy #dieletzentagedespatriarchats

⭐бракоразводный процесс анджелины джоли и брэда питта длится уже два года. актёры сделали много резких заявлений, но позднее договорились не раскрывать деталей судебного разбирательства. экс-супруги не могли урегулировать вопросы опеки над детьми. теперь актёрам удалось прийти к соглашению – об этом сообщила адвокат саманта блэй диджин. портал e! опубликовал заявление юриста, в котором она призналась, что договоренность была достигнута две недели назад, а теперь бывшие супруги подписали все необходимые бумаги. впрочем, детали соглашения юрист не стала раскрывать, сославшись на интересы детей.
🗯️💬💭
⭐26 ноября дэвид бекхэм с дочкой харпер сходил на рождественский фестиваль winter wonderland, который проходит в лондоне. папа и дочка прогулялись по гайд-парку, а затем отправились на каток. дэвид наблюдал за харпер, выкладывая фото и видео в свой instagram. он показал, как девочка катается на коньках. позже бекхэм присоединился к ней на катке и сделал совместное селфи. на фото звездный папа целует дочку в губы.
🗯️💬💭
⭐на днях белла хадид стала гостьей рекламного мероприятия компании по производству часов tag heuer в малайзии. ведущая вечера спросила беллу о стрессовых ситуациях на работе, на что модель рассказала о худшем дне в своей карьере. это произошло во время одного модного показа: «прямо перед выходом на сцену на моём платье сломалась молния. ко мне подбежали ассистенты и стали с силой её застёгивать. они делали это так, что у меня пошла кровь. мне приходилось идти по подиуму со спокойной улыбкой и прикрывать кровавое пятно». белла сказала, что после показа перед ней никто не извинился за ситуацию.

there is a shift in your relationship with your body that comes with age 🤷🏻‍♀️ a feeling of surrender (in a good way) mixed with a “what the hell” 🤷🏻‍♀️ it’s not free though 👆🏻it has come with experiences and 🙌 by resisting the urge to follow a culture that tells you that you are never good enough 👉👉👉because you’re too old or too fat or too skinny or you don’t have enough curves or have too many wrinkles and tells you that you need a boob job or a nose job and let’s not even get started with the #metoo experiences that made us hate our bodies even more 🙄 (i’ve talked too much about mine as it is and i am done with that) 🤷🏻‍♀️ healing and acceptance and loving ourselves the way we are is hard shit for sure but do it anyway 💫💜💛🧡 and yes that’s a pic of 📷📸 my ass because i feel proud of it 🤷🏻‍♀️ at 50 this is it and i’m good with that 😁👯‍♀️ happy  sunday ☀️ beautiful women all over 💫 love and respect yourself be the #goddess that you want to be 💫 and repeat after me: i’m beautiful exactly as i am 🧡💜💛🙏💫
.
.

text:
day 2 #dogoodthischristmas 
who am i? and what is unique about me? it is not easy to unravel these layers, but so important for our mental well-being. this is what we focussed on in our last #femchats session. it was an inspiring evening talking about feminism, feminist art, why we are all really feminists, gender equality, and how art can be used not only for mindfulness but self-expression and activism. so empowering to have space and time to share ideas, books, and be creative. i felt thoughtful but also so optimistic. .
.
//
if you are in or around #liverpool join our next one at @cassart1984 on 15 december. take an empowering #creativepause in between christmas shopping and bring friends. there will be mince pies! 💥💪🤛🏼🎄🌲🎁 link in profile ⬆️⬆️ or just ask! .
this is part of our ‘do good this christmas’ because proceeds go to the homeless shelter that we volunteer at over christmas.
. .
//

text:
2 1/2 years ago i was raped...
.
i was 14
and in a relationship with an abusive man
he yelled at me
he threatened me
i was horrified of him
sex was a given. i didn't have an option
i was too scared to leave
too scared to be alone
.
he told me he'd kill himself if i left
he wouldn't let me go out with my friends
he completely controlled my life in every aspect
.
for years i dealt with panic attacks, flashbacks, nightmares, extreme anxiety, and self harm
.
but now, 2 1/2 years later i'm finally ready to talk about it
about the thing that scarred me forever
because i want to tell you, you're not alone
and it doesn't have to be like this
you can get out
you can have healthy, happy relationships
you can heal
.
emdr saved my life and i'm no longer diagnosed or dealing with ptsd, but the rape and the relationship changed my life forever
.
it took years for me to heal. to see that this has a purposes
and this is why now i will be including finding and growing healthy relationships in my coaching
because i've been there, and i want to help you get out of it
i want to help you see the purpose. to see the light. to heal. to grow.
.
if you who also have been sexually assulted or in a toxic relationship, i want you to know, there's a light on the other end, even if you can't see it right now. i want you to know you're not alone. thousands of women stand by you, including me. together we will heal. together we will grow. together we will change the world
.
finding and growing healthy relationships will now be included in my coaching, because it doesn't have to be like this. i want to help you find and grow healthy relationships and get out of the toxic ones
.
you are not alone
i see you
i feel you
i believe you
#metoo

text:
i'll be in the mountains in utah this week for a healing retreat. the farthest west i've been is des moines, iowa.

this retreat is specifically for women who are survivors of childhood sexual abuse. i get to learn more ways to help me heal. from tai chi to cooking. i might even get a makeover?! it's pretty exciting but surreal!

because it's a retreat for survivors, safety is everything so i won't be sharing my journey while i'm there. i'll take pics and talk more about it once i'm back home. but i just wanted to share my excitement and nervousness with you all. i've never done anything like this but i'm open. i'm ready.

healing is a never ending journey for me. a cyclical one that rolls over the highs and the lows, always moving forward.

this stunning picture is by my talented friend @parkerspics313 and my makeup is done by the one and only @lybartistryofficial who both generously gave me their time, energy and love just to make my vision project journey come to life. a self reflection on healing from my traumas. i wrote a blog post on it back in march - website link in bio.

well this post is long as hell. i'm so grateful for all of you always supporting me! i can't wait to learn and grow. i hope to come back renewed and empowered to continue my work inside and out!

happy sunday if you made it this far!

#healingispossible #healingjourney #metoo #believesurvivors #iamasurvivor #grateful #mindbodysoul #spiritualjourney

text:
finlandiya’da 'kadın hattı' adlı kuruluş, kadınlara yönelik şiddete dikkat çekmek için sanatsal bir kampanya başlattı.

kampanya, finlandiya’nın bağımsızlık günü olan 6 aralık’ta helsinki’deki sarayda düzenlenecek kutlama ile başlayacak.
kampanya kapsamında cinsel taciz ve tecavüzlere uğrayan 3 kadının #metoo kampanyası sırasında gazetelerde yayımlanan anlatımları kadın sanatçılar ve siyasetçiler tarafından seslendirilecek.
finlandiya’nın tanınmış moda tasarımcısı anni-mari pahkala ise kadınların anlatımlarını sembolize eden balo kıyafetleri tasarlayacak.

pahkala’nın tasarladığı kıyafetler finlandiya’nın kurtuluş günü nedeniyle sarayda düzenlenecek baloda giyilecek.
pahkala, şiddete uğrayan 3 kadın için 3 ayrı balo kıyafeti tasarladı. ‘hi̇ç ki̇mse kadinlari susturma hakkina sahi̇p olmamali’
pahkala’nın tasarladığı kırmızı giysiyi giyecek olan çevre partisi yeşiller milletvekili emma kari, 10 yıl süreyle eşinin fiziki ve psikolojik şiddetine maruz kalan 3 çocuk annesi bir kadının anlatımlarını okuyacak.

finlandiya’nın kurtuluş günü dolayısıyla sarayda düzenlenen balolarda ülkede yaşanan olumsuzlukları konuşmama geleneği, emma kari’nin kendisine yapılan teklifi tereddütle karşılamasına neden olmuş.

fiziki ve psikolojik şiddete uğrayan her kadının bunu duyurma hakkı olduğuna karar veren kari, “artık hiç kimse bu kadınları susturma hakkına sahip olmamalı.

bizlerin görevi onları dinlemek, yaşamlarını sürdürebilmeleri için destek vermek ve yardım etmektir” dedi.
 sanat projeleri̇ i̇çi̇nde en sarsicisi
şiddete uğrayan 50 kadının anlatımlarını okuduğunu söyleyen moda tasarımcısı anne-mari pahkala, “bu proje bugüne kadar yer aldığım sanat projeleri içinde en sarsıcısıydı.

3 giysiyi sıkıntı içinde acı duyarak tasarladım” dedi.
name: Laiila Magazin

text:
tydligheten i detta diagram.
******************
fortsättningen på #metoo är feministisk politik 
#metoo-kampanjen har satt ljuset på omfattningen av det sexuella våldet mot kvinnor. – det hoppingivande med #metoo är att det som feminister berättat om i decennier blir tydligt för flera: vi lever fortfarande i ett patriarkalt samhälle och det skapar strukturella problem i alla våra relationer, från de mest intima och ut i de samhälleliga. vi behöver en ny kultur i politiken där vi definierar makt som något annat än strävan efter kontroll och dominans. vi behöver sociala reformer, skärpt lagstiftning, omfördelning av ekonomiska resurser och en politik som på allvar erkänner att kvinnors rättigheter är mänskliga rättigheter. fortsättningen på #metoo är feministisk politik, säger gudrun schyman.

text:
голливудские актрисы стали героинями нового номера американского журнала the holywood reporter. для обложки снялись леди гага, николь кидман,кэтрин хан, гленн клоуз, регина кинг и рэйчел вайс.

для фотосессии они примерили наряды в красных оттенках. так, 32-летняя леди гага была в платье с отдельными рукавами, 51-летняя николь кидман и 47-летняя регина кинг — в платьях с пайетками, 45-летняя кэтрин хан — в пиджаке, 71-летняя гленн клоуз выбрала шелковый костюм, а 48-летняя рэйчел вайс сделала ставку на платье с запахом.
актрисы собрались за круглым столом,чтобы обсудить положение женщин в кинематографе и движение #metoo по защите от харассмента.
так, леди гага размышляла об уязвимости, силе и о том, как непросто«идти вглубь того, кто вы есть». она призналась, что до сих пор отходит от своей роли в фильме «звезда родилась»: «я все еще чувствую, что восстанавливаюсь».
николь кидман заявила, что готова делиться любой информацией с молодыми актрисами и помогать не только советами, но и материально. а рэйчел вайс считает, что девочки должны расти «на историях, в которых у женщины центральная роль». #звездныеновости#шоубиз#звезды#почитаем#новостизвезд#длявсех#шоубизнесс#шок#сплетни#знаменитости#звезда#новости#главныеновости
name: 🌟🌟🌟новости звезд🌟🌟🌟

text:
rising: east of eden (6/14) by nicholas jones, 28 november 2016. -

you once told me that someone feeling love pains,
is capable of self-degradation in the most unbelievable ways,
and certain liquids gave birth to certain lapses of judgment,
and it seemed as though i found love in the most hopeless places,
maybe that’s why i write about love all the time,
because i want it more than anything else,

we sat on your couch and stayed up until five,
talking about vintage cars and old hollywood guys,
then you flashed that smile that you so often wear,
whenever you were with me and i never cared,
we watched the sun come up over the clouds,
and then i fell upwards and never came down,
and you put on that same old movie you always played,
east of eden was never too far away,

you were the first man that i ever loved,
fate took its turn and tragedy struck,
so they buried you way out past highway six,
where you taught me how to drive your stick shift,
and i look in the mirror each and everyday,
and i’ve yet to find a part of me that,
hasn’t been touched by you in some way,

so i went back to my bed and laid there still,
and i thought that watching east of eden,
could have brought my head right back to your chest,
and i would have watched it again and again,
without hesitation - because you were just the best,
the academy award for the most beautiful mess,
because all of the great and precious things in this world are lonely,
and so now i suppose that you were lonely too,

there’s a tragic beauty in the element of truth,
and should the truth be told - i always loved you,
your iconic gaze gave way to faith that someday,
i’d love you in a special way - two hearts entombed,
in shallow graves for fire signs that set the world ablaze,
just east of eden at the intersection of glory days and memory lane. -
